<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-576-714  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 576 714.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  August 28 1989 n330 p69(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Jockeying for OEMs: forward pricing is vendors' ace in the hole.andO;(hard-drive vendors)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gillooly, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Hard-drive vendors are practicing forward-pricing techniques andoffering low-margin prices in an attempt to win accounts.andP;  Drivemanufacturers practicing forward pricing sell their products tosystem vendors at the price a disk drive would sell for at thesystem-house level.andP;  Forward pricing is used most when two vendorsare competing for the same supply contract.andP;  The method has beenpracticed in the industry for about a year already, although it isnot confined to the drive industry.andP;  However, the fact that it isbeing coupled with pricing incentives is increasing competition.andO;One marketing manager for a microcomputer vendor claims drivemanufacturers are trying to convince their customers to sell morestandard configurations with hard-disk drives.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     VendorsPricing PolicyOEMsDisk DrivesMarketing StrategyHard Disk.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>